concludeQuestions.improve: Take more measurements at each site since there is a fair amount of scatter for shear strength between repeat measurements

consistent-reason.value: I started with 3 measurements since I thought there would not be a large variation between individual measurements at each site. After observing the graph for initial sampling, I think between 5 and 10 measurements at each location would have been a better choice

evenly-space-reason.value: Since the graph in the hypothesis seems to suggest a steady slope, that should be obtainable from a few, equally spaced points and a higher location density would only be helpful to identify the location of the point of saturation, where the graph flattens out, which could be done once the two points between which it occurred were identified.
